Identification. The adult specimen (
Fig. 1 c
) largely agreed with the description provided by
Ziegler ( 2002 )
. Sequence congruence between the adult specimen ( ZFMK 86372 ) and tadpoles ( ZFMK 86987, 86988;
Fig. 2 c
) was 100 %. The following larval description is based on a single tadpole in Gosner stage 27 (
Fig. 5
; for measurements see
Table 6
). The tadpole specimen used for description and drawing originates from the same water body as the DNA voucher specimen. In this water body, no other
Hylarana
species were observed. The DNA voucher specimen was destroyed for DNA extraction but examined morphologically before this procedure, and it fully agreed morphologically with the described and drawn specimen in the diagnostic characters (narrow upper jaw sheath, cone-shaped marginal papillae, one submarginal row of papillae, papillae unpigmented, silver-white colour with dark dorsoventral stripe). The identification of the described specimen is therefore well supported.
